result.execSummary:
The defendant Earl Autrey Blish was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Earl Autrey Blish is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Earl Autrey Blish was found guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Earl Autrey Blish was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
AND ARRAIGNMENT 10:07 AM Defendant Earl Autrey Blish in court, in custody.  Attorney Ellen Denise Craker in court for Earl Autrey Blish.  Attorney Chad C La Lor in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. State recites agreement: pleas to count 1 and 2. Count 3 is dismissed. 57 day jail concurrent on each count. 43 days credit; time served with good time. $150 fine plus costs. 
Attorney Craker indicates that complaint has been received and waives reading. 
Defendant pleads guilty to count 1 and count 2. Attorney Craker indicates a stipulation to a factual basis. Court finds that the defendant's plea is knowingly and voluntarily made. Court accepts the plea and finds the defendant guilty. Judgment of convictions are entered. Count 3 is dismissed. 
State recites defendant's criminal history and asks that the court adopt the joint recommendation. Attorney Craker has nothing further.
Court orders on each count 57 day jail concurrent on each count with 43 days credit; time served with good time. $150 fine plus costs and surcharges. 120 days to pay or payment plan through Clerk of Court's office.

records.addlTxt: No use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription.

3:53 PM Defendant Earl Autrey Blish appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Angela Wilson  in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Ellen Craker appeared via video for defendant. Attorney Craker recieved complaint, waives reading and requests preliminary hearing. State requests $2,500 cash bail with condition of no use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription. Criminal history out of several states and a pending warrant out of Montana. Defendant has a Montana drivers license and vehicle registered out of North Dakota. Defendant has criminal history out of several states. Attorney Craker notes defendant qualifies. Does not find cash necessary and notes defendant is homeless. The criminal history is dated. Defendant is not able to post cash bail and gave a North Dakota mailing address. Defendant notes he moved here recently for a change and moved into an apartment but isn't living there yet. Court orders $2,500 cash bail with condition of no use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for April 13, 2022 at 11:30 am.
